I've seen 2-10 times figure mentioned as a reasonable expectation for this. (I hit around 5-6x on my last few projects.)

Avoid calling back into R (i.e., Rcpp::Function) too frequently, because crossing that interpreter boundary carries a real price.

Also, if your R code is mostly staying inside its C library (e.g., matrix ops), rewriting it in Armadillo won't make much difference since it only speeds up a very thin outside layer.

Davor


